<% set_meta_tags title: "The Making of pastehtml.dev — A Human & an AI Build a Thing", description: "One human, one AI, one late night and one full day — the lightly edited but faithful transcript of how pastehtml.dev went from an idea to a deployed product, including the typo that decided the entire design." %>
<div class="vanity-page">
<style>
  /* ===== Shared template: base chrome (scoped to .vanity-page) ===== */
  :root {
    --ink: #18120e;
    --paper: #fff8ec;
    --red: #e62429;
    --yellow: #ffd400;
    --blue: #0072ce;
  }
  .vanity-page, .vanity-page * { margin: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  .vanity-page {
    background-color: var(--paper);
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(circle at 25% 15%, rgb(255 212 0 / 0.18), transparent 42%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 85% 80%, rgb(0 114 206 / 0.10), transparent 45%),
      radial-gradient(circle, rgb(24 18 14 / 0.07) 1px, transparent 1.4px);
    background-size: auto, auto, 12px 12px;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: Inter, "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .vanity-page .wrap { max-width: 56rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem; }
  .vanity-page .bangers { font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
  .vanity-page .mono { font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; }

  /* Hero */
  .vanity-page header { text-align: center; padding: 2rem 0 3rem; position: relative; }
  .vanity-page .logo {
    display: inline-block; background: #fff; border: 3px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 0 var(--ink); padding: 0.2rem 1.1rem; transform: rotate(-2deg);
    font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;
    transition: transform 120ms ease, box-shadow 120ms ease;
  }
  .vanity-page .logo:hover { transform: rotate(-2deg) translate(-1px, -1px); box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 0 var(--ink); }
  .vanity-page .logo:active { transform: rotate(-2deg) translate(2px, 2px); box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 0 var(--ink); }
  .vanity-page .logo span { color: var(--red); }
  .vanity-page h1 {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 9vw, 5.5rem); line-height: 1.02; margin-top: 1.5rem;
    text-shadow: 3px 3px 0 var(--paper), 6px 6px 0 var(--red); text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .vanity-page .sub {
    margin: 1.25rem auto 0; max-width: 42ch; color: rgb(24 18 14 / 0.7); font-size: 1.05rem; text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .vanity-page .badge-row { margin-top: 1.5rem; display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .vanity-page .chip {
    background: var(--yellow); border: 2px solid var(--ink); box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 0 var(--ink);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.7rem; font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; transform: rotate(-1deg);
  }
  .vanity-page .chip:nth-child(2n) { transform: rotate(1.2deg); background: #fff; }
  .vanity-page .burst {
    position: absolute; top: -0.5rem; right: 0; width: 110px; transform: rotate(14deg);
    filter: drop-shadow(3px 3px 0 var(--ink));
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .vanity-page .burst { width: 78px; right: -0.25rem; } }

  /* Chapters */
  .vanity-page .issue { margin: 4rem 0 1.75rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; }
  .vanity-page .issue::before, .vanity-page .issue::after { content: ""; flex: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--ink); }
  .vanity-page .issue h2 {
    font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.03em; font-size: 1.7rem;
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.25rem 1.2rem;
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 0 var(--red); transform: rotate(-1deg); text-align: center;
  }

  /* Bubbles */
  .vanity-page .msg { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; margin: 1.4rem 0; align-items: flex-start; }
  .vanity-page .msg.ali { flex-direction: row-reverse; }
  .vanity-page .avatar {
    flex-shrink: 0; width: 2.6rem; height: 2.6rem; border: 3px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid; place-items: center; font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; font-size: 1.3rem;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 0 var(--ink); margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .ali .avatar { background: var(--yellow); }
  .vanity-page .claude .avatar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; }
  .vanity-page .bubble {
    position: relative; max-width: 44rem; border: 3px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.15rem; box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 0 var(--ink); font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .ali .bubble { background: #fff7d6; border-top-right-radius: 4px; }
  .vanity-page .claude .bubble { background: #fff; border-top-left-radius: 4px; }
  .vanity-page .who {
    font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; font-size: 0.95rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .ali .who { color: #8a6d00; }
  .vanity-page .claude .who { color: var(--red); }
  .vanity-page .bubble p + p { margin-top: 0.55rem; }
  .vanity-page .bubble code {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; font-size: 0.83em; background: rgb(24 18 14 / 0.07);
    border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.05rem 0.3rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .did {
    margin-top: 0.7rem; padding-top: 0.65rem; border-top: 2px dashed rgb(24 18 14 / 0.2);
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .did span {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    background: rgb(0 114 206 / 0.1); border: 1.5px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.55rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .did .t { background: var(--yellow); font-weight: 600; }
  .vanity-page .when {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    background: #fff; border: 2px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 999px;
    box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 0 var(--ink); padding: 0.15rem 0.7rem; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .vanity-page .nap {
    text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0; font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem; color: rgb(24 18 14 / 0.6); letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .vanity-page .asks { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 0.25rem; display: grid; gap: 0.5rem; counter-reset: ask; }
  .vanity-page .asks li { position: relative; padding-left: 1.7rem; }
  .vanity-page .asks li::before {
    counter-increment: ask; content: counter(ask);
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.22rem; width: 1.1rem; height: 1.1rem;
    background: var(--yellow); border: 2px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 5px;
    display: grid; place-items: center; font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 700;
  }
  .vanity-page .volley {
    border: 3px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 14px; box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 0 var(--ink);
    background: #fff; overflow: hidden; margin: 1.6rem 0;
  }
  .vanity-page .v-title {
    font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.04em; font-size: 1.15rem;
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); padding: 0.35rem 1rem;
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; gap: 1rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .v-title .mono { font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgb(255 248 236 / 0.7); letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .vanity-page .v-row { padding: 0.7rem 1rem; display: grid; gap: 0.3rem; font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .vanity-page .v-row + .v-row { border-top: 2px dashed rgb(24 18 14 / 0.18); }
  .vanity-page .v-row b {
    font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    font-size: 0.85rem; margin-right: 0.35rem;
  }
  .vanity-page .v-ask b { color: #8a6d00; } .vanity-page .v-fix b { color: var(--red); }
  .vanity-page .v-fix i { font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", "IBM Plex Sans Arabic", monospace; font-style: normal; font-size: 0.68rem; color: rgb(24 18 14 / 0.55); margin-left: 0.3rem; }
  .vanity-page .pow {
    font-family: Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif; color: var(--red); font-size: 1.05em;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .vanity-page footer {
    margin-top: 5rem; text-align: center; border-top: 3px solid var(--ink); padding-top: 2rem;
  }
  .vanity-page footer .bangers { font-size: 2.2rem; text-shadow: 2px 2px 0 var(--paper), 4px 4px 0 var(--red); }
  .vanity-page footer p { color: rgb(24 18 14 / 0.65); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .vanity-page footer a { color: var(--blue); font-weight: 600; text-underline-offset: 4px; text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }

  /* ===== Bilingual: EN | عربي ===== */
  .vanity-page [hidden] { display: none !important; }

  /* Arabic is cursive — neutralize every display letter-spacing so letters join. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] * { letter-spacing: normal; }
  /* Keep code and the log-style timestamps as isolated LTR runs inside Arabic. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] code, .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .mono, .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .when,
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .did .t, .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .v-title .mono, .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .v-fix i {
    unicode-bidi: isolate;
  }
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] code { direction: ltr; }
  /* Mirror the chat-bubble tails to match the flipped avatar sides. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .ali .bubble { border-top-right-radius: 14px; border-top-left-radius: 4px; }
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .claude .bubble { border-top-left-radius: 14px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; }
  /* Numbered "asks" markers move to the right edge. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .asks li { padding-left: 0; padding-right: 1.7rem; }
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .asks li::before { left: auto; right: 0; }
  /* Flip directional spacing. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .v-row b { margin-right: 0; margin-left: 0.35rem; }
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .v-fix i { margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0.3rem; }
  /* The starburst sits top-left in RTL. */
  .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .burst { right: auto; left: 0; transform: rotate(-14deg); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .vanity-page [dir="rtl"] .burst { left: -0.25rem; right: auto; } }
</style>

<div class="wrap" id="en" data-lang="en"<%= " hidden" if I18n.locale == :ar %>>

<header>
  <svg class="burst" viewBox="0 0 120 120" aria-hidden="true">
    <polygon fill="#e62429" stroke="#18120e" stroke-width="3"
      points="60,4 71,26 93,13 91,38 116,37 99,55 120,68 96,74 105,98 81,90 78,115 60,96 42,115 39,90 15,98 24,74 0,68 21,55 4,37 29,38 27,13 49,26"/>
    <text text-anchor="middle" font-family="Bangers, Lalezar, Impact, sans-serif" font-size="21" fill="#fff" transform="rotate(-8 60 60)"><tspan x="60" y="56">True</tspan><tspan x="60" y="76">story!</tspan></text>
  </svg>
  <h1 class="bangers">The Making Of</h1>
  <p class="sub">One human, one AI, one late night and one full day. The (lightly edited, otherwise faithful)
     transcript of how pastehtml.dev went from an idea to a deployed product — including the typo that decided
     the entire design.</p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="chip">Ali — the human</span>
    <span class="chip">Claude — the AI</span>
    <span class="chip">Rails 8 · Hotwire · Kamal</span>
    <span class="chip">⏱ ≈4¾h build time over 18h</span>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="issue"><h2>Issue #1 — The Origin Story</h2><span class="when">01:20 → 01:55 AM</span></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>I want to build a website named pastehtml.dev. Create HTML files quickly and share links with my friends.
     No signup/signin — just drag and drop a file and get a link. Preview or view source. No one can edit or
     delete created files. Unique, hard-to-guess IDs. Build it following <strong>marbel</strong> style design.
     Rails, PostgreSQL, Tailwind, esbuild — follow my faqieh app's conventions. Do your best, I trust you.
     Don't stop unless you finished everything.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Read "marbel" as <em>marble</em>. Built the entire app in one go: dockerized postgres (port 5435 — three
     other apps had taken the neighbors), a <code>Paste</code> model with unguessable tokens, drag-and-drop
     upload, share links, a sandboxed preview (user HTML runs but can never touch the site), and an elegant
     white-marble design with serif headlines. Tests green, security scan clean, running on port 3000.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 01:20–01:45 · ≈25 min</span><span>full Rails app</span><span>CSP sandbox</span><span>marble UI</span><span>19 tests</span></div>
</div></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Hmmm, I think it works but the design — I meant to say <strong>marvel</strong>. I want it very modern and
     developer friendly. Make it fancy.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p><span class="pow">The great retcon!</span> Asked which Marvel — Ali picked comic-book energy. Rebuilt the whole
     look: Bangers display type with hard red shadows, ink-outlined panels, Ben-Day halftone dots, a FREE!
     starburst on the drop zone, and a footer signed "issue #1". Same app, infinitely more <em>kapow</em>.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 01:45–01:55 · ≈12 min</span><span>comic redesign</span><span>halftone + starbursts</span><span>comic favicon</span></div>
</div></div>

<div class="issue"><h2>Issue #2 — The Polish Saga</h2><span class="when">01:55 AM → 12:52 PM</span></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Add source code highlighting. And let users make the preview fullscreen — but <em>inside</em> the
     website: keep some border so you know you're still on the site.</p>
</div></div>
<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Server-side syntax highlighting (Rouge, zero JS), and the preview became a faux browser window —
     traffic-light dots, filename in the title bar — that expands to fill the viewport while staying visibly
     inside the site.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 01:55–01:59 · ≈5 min</span><span>Rouge highlighting</span><span>in-site fullscreen</span></div>
</div></div>
<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Make the IDs longer — 32 chars maybe. Also, when I exit fullscreen, keep the scroll as it is;
     right now it jumps to the top.</p>
</div></div>
<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Tokens grew to 32 characters (~165 bits — nobody is guessing one), and the scroll position is saved on
     entry and restored on exit, so the page stays exactly where you left it.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 02:00–02:03 · ≈3 min</span><span>32-char tokens</span><span>scroll restore</span></div>
</div></div>
<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Use the UI and transitions skills to review the whole thing. Add polished touches and transitions.
     Make it great and mobile responsive.</p>
</div></div>
<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>A drawn-on-load success checkmark, panels that slide in with a cross-blur, the copy button cross-fading
     to "Copied!", page-to-page view transitions — every animation with a reduced-motion guard. The mobile audit
     caught real bugs: the headline's comic shadow collided with itself on small screens, and a rogue starburst
     caused a 1px horizontal scroll. Both fixed.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 02:03–02:10 · ≈8 min</span><span>success check</span><span>panel reveal</span><span>mobile fixes</span></div>
</div></div>
<p class="nap">💤 02:10 AM — Ali goes to sleep. The repo waits patiently. — back at 12:36 PM 💤</p>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Now allow users to go fullscreen by pressing <code>F</code> (no Shift or anything).</p>
</div></div>
<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Plain <code>F</code> toggles fullscreen — but never while you're typing in a field, never hijacking
     Cmd+F, and never while the preview is hidden behind the Source tab.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 12:36–12:38 · ≈3 min</span><span>F shortcut</span></div>
</div></div>
<div class="volley">
  <div class="v-title">The fullscreen animation goes four rounds <span class="mono">12:39 → 12:52</span></div>
  <div class="v-row">
    <p class="v-ask"><b>ALI</b> The enter/exit animation is not good. Polish it.</p>
    <p class="v-fix"><b>CLAUDE</b> Modal-style open and close: the backdrop fades while the panel scales, with a softer two-phase exit. <i>12:39</i></p>
  </div>
  <div class="v-row">
    <p class="v-ask"><b>ALI</b> Still not right — the inline card gets removed then re-added. You can see it disappear and reappear. Looks bad.</p>
    <p class="v-fix"><b>CLAUDE</b> Reserved the card's space and made it morph: it now visibly grows out of its spot in the page and shrinks back, never blinking out. <i>12:45</i></p>
  </div>
  <div class="v-row">
    <p class="v-ask"><b>ALI</b> It's great now! But the Fullscreen/Exit button makes the transition weird — its size changes.</p>
    <p class="v-fix"><b>CLAUDE</b> Both labels now stack in one slot, so the button keeps a constant width and just cross-fades. <i>12:48</i></p>
  </div>
  <div class="v-row">
    <p class="v-ask"><b>ALI</b> One more — it's the whole top bar that resizes when the card comes back from fullscreen. Thoughts?</p>
    <p class="v-fix"><b>CLAUDE</b> Root cause found: scale transforms squash fixed-height bars. Rewrote the morph as a true window-zoom that animates real geometry — the toolbar measured a constant 47px through the whole animation. <i>12:51</i></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="issue"><h2>Issue #3 — Going Public</h2><span class="when">12:52 → 13:35</span></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <ul class="asks">
  <li>Do a full review of the codebase — simplify, remove dead code, refactor.</li>
  <li>Then add, following faqieh's patterns: a PWA with best practices, custom 404/500/422 pages, an OG image, and SEO meta tags.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Trimmed five unused Rails frameworks and three gems, fixed a CI workflow that would never have passed, then
     shipped the public face: installable PWA (minimal network-first service worker, comic offline page, maskable
     icons), comic-styled error pages for every status, and a generated 1200×630 OG banner with proper meta tags.
     Verified the offline page by actually killing the server mid-browse.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 12:52–13:15 · ≈23 min</span><span>−5 frameworks</span><span>PWA + offline</span><span>comic error pages</span><span>OG banner</span></div>
</div></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <ul class="asks">
  <li>I think the favicon and the other icons are not matching, no?</li>
  <li>About the PWA splash icon: in faqieh it has a different background than the splash and sharp edges — it looks ugly. Rounded would be great. Thoughts?</li>
  <li>Do the fix for faqieh too, while we're at it.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Sharp eye — the favicon's "P" was a serif fallback because SVG text can't load web fonts. Extracted the real
     Bangers glyph as a vector path and rebuilt every icon from it. Then proved with pixel checks that pastehtml's
     splash icon already had transparent rounded corners (the good case), explained the any-vs-maskable mechanics,
     and patched faqieh's icon build script so its splash stops showing a sharp mismatched block.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 13:20–13:35 · ≈15 min (faqieh included)</span><span>Bangers glyph → vector</span><span>icons unified</span><span>faqieh fixed too</span></div>
</div></div>

<div class="issue"><h2>Issue #4 — The Agent Awakens</h2><span class="when">13:38 → 14:31</span></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Do you know why I built this? ... Right — I built it to share generated design documents and implementation
     plans from AI agents. Based on that, what do you think of the current state? What should we do next?</p>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Called it: the workflow smelled like sharing AI-generated artifacts. The gap was that publishing was
     human-only. So: a JSON API (<code>curl -F file=@plan.html pastehtml.dev/api/pastes</code> → share link),
     paste-from-clipboard with ⌘V (including copied <em>files</em> from Finder, after Ali caught that one),
     <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> extraction so links read like documents, and rate limits + SSL + host protection
     for production.</p>
  <div class="did"><span class="t">⏱ 13:38–13:55 · ≈17 min</span><span>agent API</span><span>⌘V publishing</span><span>title extraction</span><span>hardening</span></div>
</div></div>

<div class="msg ali"><div class="avatar">A</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">ALI</div>
  <p>Should agents be able to <em>update</em> pastes? I was thinking about a contract — the API returns a second
     token, and that token can update the paste later. Thoughts?</p>
</div></div>

<div class="msg claude"><div class="avatar">C</div><div class="bubble">
  <div class="who">CLAUDE</div>
  <p>Endorsed the capability-token contract, flagged the two collisions (the "sealed forever" promise and the
     1-year cache), laid out options — Ali chose in-place updates. Shipped: an <code>update_token</code> revealed
